LuaScript:
Events = {
  onObjectPickUp = "onObjectPickUp",
  onObjectEnterZone = "onObjectEnterZone"
}

----#include <injections.ttslua>
do

GlobalInjections = {}

local function addInjection(injections_table, event, func)
  if injections_table[event] == nil then
    injections_table[event] = {}
  end
  table.insert(injections_table[event], func)
end

function addObjectInjection(object, event, func)
  if object.events_injections == nil then
    object.events_injections = {}
  end
  addInjection(object.events_injections, event, func)
end

function addGlobalInjection(event, func)
  addInjection(GlobalInjections, event, func)
end

function getObjectInjections(object, event)
  return object.events_injections[event]
end

function getGlobalInjections(event)
  return GlobalInjections[event]
end

local function applyInjections(injections_table, event, ...)
  if injections_table == nil then return end
  if injections_table[event] == nil then return end

  local injections = injections_table[event]
  for _, injection in ipairs(injections) do
    injection(...)
  end
end

function applyGlobalInjections(event, ...)
  applyInjections(GlobalInjections, event, ...)
end

function applyObjectInjections(object, event, ...)
  applyInjections(object.events_injections, event, ...)
end

end

do
local cloning_source_tag = "cloning_source"

local function executeCloning(object)
  local clone = object.clone()
  clone.setPosition(object.getPosition())
  clone.addTag(cloning_source_tag)
  object.removeTag(cloning_source_tag)
end

local function cloningInjection(colorName, object)
  if object.hasTag(cloning_source_tag) then
    executeCloning(object)
  end
end

addGlobalInjection(Events.onObjectPickUp, cloningInjection)

end

function onObjectPickUp(colorName, object)

end

function onObjectEnterZone(zone, object)
  applyGlobalInjections(Events.onObjectEnterZone, zone, object)
end

ObjectStates.LuaScript:
function onLoad()
  math.randomseed(os.time())
  self.addContextMenuItem("Roll", roll)
end

function roll(player_color, position, object)
  self.addForce(vector(0, 20, 0))
  -- Use random generated torgue is wrong way. By unclear reason random generated torgue almost always leads to roll same face.
  changeFace = math.random() > 0.5
  if (changeFace)
  then
  self.addTorque(vector(0.42, 0.16, 0.33))
  else
    self.addTorque(vector(0.52, 0.48, 0.93))
  end
end

ObjectStates.Name: ScriptingTrigger
ObjectStates.LuaScript:
----#include <counter_zone.ttslua>
do
local counter_zone_tag = "counter_zone"

thickness = 0.125
color = color(0.8, 0.1, 0.1, 1.0)
textId = nil
textSize = 72
valueKey = "denomination"

local function updateValue()
  local objects = self.getObjects()
  local total = 0
  for i, o in ipairs(objects) do
    local value = o.getVar(valueKey)
    local count = o.getQuantity()
    count = (count == -1) and 1 or count
    if value != nil then
      total = total + value * count
    end
  end
  getObjectFromGUID(textId).setValue("" .. total)
end

function onLoad()
  --Make an X above the middle of the table
  local pos = self.getPosition()
  local scale = self.getScale()
  local y = pos.y - scale.y / 2
  local p1 = {pos.x - scale.x / 2, y, pos.z - scale.z / 2}
  local p2 = {pos.x + scale.x / 2, y, pos.z - scale.z / 2}
  local p3 = {pos.x + scale.x / 2, y, pos.z + scale.z / 2}
  local p4 = {pos.x - scale.x / 2, y, pos.z + scale.z / 2}
  local border =   {
      points    = { p1, p2, p3, p4, p1},
      color     = color,
      thickness = thickness,
      rotation  = {0,0,0},
  }
  local existLines = Global.getVectorLines()
  existLines = (existLines != nil) and existLines or {}
  table.insert(existLines, border)
  Global.setVectorLines(existLines)

  local text = getObjectFromGUID(textId)
  text.TextTool.setFontColor(color)
  text.TextTool.setFontSize(textSize)
  updateValue()
end

function onObjectEnterZone(zone, object)
    updateValue()
end

function onObjectLeaveZone(zone, object)
    updateValue()
end


--addGlobalInjection(Events.onObjectEnterZone, updateValue)

end
